    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the overview. i guess i'm just wondering why certain people think it should be in the school at all instead of just at home. it feels like some people act like it's just a matter of common sense to include it, while others are being treated like they're just being difficult. is there a specific reason why the inclusive side is usually seen as the more 'modern' or 'correct' approach in these discussions?",
